# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# ATL-AI Orchestrator — Environment Configuration
# Copy this to .env and fill in your values.
# All variables use the ATL_ prefix (Pydantic auto-strips it).
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── App ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
ATL_APP_NAME=ATL-AI Orchestrator
ATL_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
ATL_DEBUG=true

# ── Authentication Mode ─────────────────────────────────
# jwt = decode locally (fast) | http = call Main App | hybrid = JWT first, HTTP fallback
ATL_AUTH_MODE=hybrid

# ── JWT (MUST match the client app's JWT secret) ────────
# This is the shared secret between the orchestrator and the client app (e.g. ERP-BGS).
# If ERP-BGS sets AI_JWT_SECRET=xxx, this must be the same value.
ATL_JWT_SECRET_OR_PUBLIC_KEY=change-me-shared-jwt-secret
ATL_JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
ATL_JWT_ISSUER=erp-bgs
ATL_JWT_AUDIENCE=atl-ai

# ── Main App Connection (for HTTP auth fallback) ────────
# The client application that sends users to this orchestrator.
ATL_MAIN_APP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:7000
ATL_MAIN_APP_VERIFY_ENDPOINT=/verify-user
ATL_TOKEN_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=300

# ── Staging Database ────────────────────────────────────
# Option A: Full URL override (e.g. SQLite for dev)
ATL_STAGING_DB_URL_OVERRIDE=sqlite+aiosqlite:///path/to/your/db.sqlite3
# Option B: Individual params (PostgreSQL for production)
# ATL_STAGING_DB_HOST=localhost
# ATL_STAGING_DB_PORT=5433
# ATL_STAGING_DB_NAME=staging
# ATL_STAGING_DB_USER=ai_reader
# ATL_STAGING_DB_PASSWORD=changeme_staging

# ── LLM Provider ────────────────────────────────────────
# Groq Cloud (https://console.groq.com/keys)
ATL_LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai
ATL_LLM_API_KEY=your-groq-api-key-here
ATL_LLM_MODEL=meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct
ATL_LLM_FAST_MODEL=openai/gpt-oss-20b
ATL_LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.1
ATL_LLM_MAX_TOKENS=8192
ATL_LLM_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120
ATL_LLM_CONTEXT_WINDOW=131072
ATL_LLM_SCHEMA_BUDGET_TOKENS=32000
ATL_LLM_HISTORY_BUDGET_TOKENS=16000

# ── Per-Department LLM Keys (optional, JSON) ────────────
# ATL_LLM_DEPARTMENT_KEYS={"HR":"sk-hr-xxx","Sales":"sk-sales-xxx"}

# ── Guardrails ──────────────────────────────────────────
ATL_PII_DETECTION_ENABLED=true
ATL_OUTPUT_VALIDATION_ENABLED=true
ATL_MAX_SQL_RETRIES=2

# ── Episodic Memory ────────────────────────────────────
ATL_EPISODIC_MEMORY_ENABLED=true
ATL_EPISODIC_MEMORY_MAX_EPISODES=50

# ── Ollama (local models, optional) ────────────────────
ATL_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434

# ── Rate Limiting ───────────────────────────────────────
ATL_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE=10

# ── Admin Panel Authentication ──────────────────────────
# Separate from the client app — this is the orchestrator's own admin system.
ATL_ADMIN_JWT_SECRET=orchestrator-admin-secret-change-me
ATL_ADMIN_JWT_TTL=28800
ATL_ADMIN_DEFAULT_USERNAME=admin
ATL_ADMIN_DEFAULT_PASSWORD=admin123
ATL_ERP_ADMIN_ROLES=admin,owner,gm

# ── Paths ───────────────────────────────────────────────
ATL_SCHEMA_MAP_PATH=schema_map.json
ATL_ROLE_CONFIG_PATH=rbac/role_config.json
